{
  "answer": "**The work is *Vrhaspatitattva* (unknown author), Chapter 1.**[^1]\n\nIn this passage, the divine instructor Śrīkaṇṭha speaks in the first person to his pupil Vṛhaspati, identifying himself within the succession and confessing his backstory.\n\n**The succession-list:** \"Ananta, Sūkṣma, Śivatama, Ekarudra, Ekanetra, Trimūrti, Śrīkaṇṭha, and Śikhaṇḍī.\" He explains: \"The holy Sūkṣma replaces Ananta, Śivatama replaces Sūkṣma, Ekarudra replaces Śivatama, Ekanetra replaces Ekarudra, Trimūrti replaces Ekanetra, Śrīkaṇṭha replaces Trimūrti, and Śikhaṇḍī replaces Śrīkaṇṭha. I am that Śrīkaṇṭha.\"[^1]\n\n**The Kāmadeva-and-Umā confession:** \"But I was shot with passion by Lord Kāma. I gazed upon the holy Kāma, and because he was gazed upon with my poison-sight, the body of the holy Kāmadeva was shattered, incinerated, and turned to ash. But the passion (*rāga*) remained in me. That is why I took your mother, the Lady Umā, as my wife, and we had a son, the holy Sanatkumāra.\"[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Vrhaspatitattva*, [p-4d2295](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/#p-4d2295).",
